INSERT INTO ForumEntries VALUES('BW0009', 2016, 1, 'P0000008O', '2017-11-28 09:06:52', 'A0000020T', '2016-07-21 11:48:26', 'We came here for brunch on a Saturday around 10:00 AM, and it was relatively full. We ordered: the Malaysian Curry Chicken with Rice ($6.50), the Malaysian Street Style Sandwich ($5.99), soy milk tea ($1.80) and the hot honey lemon juice ($1.80). The Malaysian Curry was delicious but really, really oily (you could literally see the pools of oil gathering on top of the bowl). If you"re fine with that (which I was), you"ll probably still enjoy it. The sandwich was our highlight - it really filling but still super light and tasty (the bread was white toast, crispy and buttered). It was stuffed with everything it promised, but it didn"t make you feel gross afterwards. With the tea, it was a great, comforting Saturday morning meal!');
INSERT INTO ForumEntries VALUES('BW0009', 2016, 1, 'P0000008O', '2017-11-28 09:06:52', 'A0000016U', '2019-09-28 03:53:11', 'Great tanning salon near me, and clean, equipped with the latest tech and easy checkin and out spot for a short yet amazing relaxation and sunbathing time in chilli Cleveland. I am going to be obsessed with this place in winters and will recharge myself with vitamin D!');
